    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I tried `make docker-compose` and got `ERROR: Couldn't connect to Docker daemon at http+docker://localhost - is it running?`.\r\nI do have `docker` installed. If I run `sudo make docker-compose`, `docker` is found and the command does what it's supposed to do.\r\n\r\nI think the reason is because a default install of `docker` will be such that `docker` will require sudo and run as root. Although it's not recommanded to run `docker` as root (and therefore the containers) for security reasons, it's up to the user to allow a non-root user to run `docker`. \r\n\r\nHere is how to run `docker` as a non-root user -> https://www.thegeekdiary.com/run-docker-as-a-non-root-user/\r\n\r\nI don't know if something needs to be done in the repo though.",
